<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>
<rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> building <rs type="objectType">block</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.34</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.47</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">
0.34</measure>) without moulding, but with a recessed edge on all sides.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p>
The inscription is cut on the face, some way down the stone, and runs into the frame on both sides.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p><measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">
0.02-0.025</measure></p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0001" notAfter="0100" exact="none">First century A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</p>
</div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="0"/><space unit="line" dim="vertical"/><lb n="1"/><w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w>  <w lemma="βουλή">βουλὴ</w>  <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w>  <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w>  <w lemma="δῆμος">δῆ<lb n="2" type="worddiv"/>μος</w>  <w lemma="τιμάω"><orig reg="ἐτίμησεν">ἐτείμησεν</orig></w><lb n="3"/><persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Μιθραδάτης">Μιθραδάτην</name>  <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Ἀθηναγόρας">Ἀθη<lb n="4" type="worddiv"/>ναγόρου</name></persName></persName>  <w lemma="ἀνήρ">ἄνδρα</w><lb n="5"/><w lemma="καλός">καλὸν</w>  <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w>  <w lemma="ἀγαθός">ἀγα<lb n="6" type="worddiv"/>θὸν</w>  <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w>  <w lemma="πᾶς">πάσῃ</w>  <w lemma="κοσμέω">κοσ<lb n="7" type="worddiv"/>μηθέντα</w>  <w lemma="ἀρετή">ἀρετῇ</w></ab>
</div>

<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Transcription (Reynolds); Gaudin/Reinach papers; publications.</p>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>The council and the people honoured Mithradates son of Athenagoras, a fine and good man, and adorned with all virtue.</p>
</div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>This text was one of a group cut on the family tomb whose elements were incorporated into the walls at the south east gate of the city: <xref type="inscription" n="1001" href="120410">12.410</xref> (= MAMA 462), <xref type="inscription" n="1010" href="130302">13.302</xref> (=474, 475, 476) and <xref type="inscription" n="369" href="120409">12.409</xref> (Walls 151) The group is published and discussed by <bibl n="jmr1991a">Reynolds 1999</bibl>.</p><p>.</p>
</div>

<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p> <rs type="origLocation">On the tomb from which it was found fallen</rs>, which had been <rs type="found">incorporated in the <rs type="monuList">Walls, South-east Gate</rs></rs>. <rs type="lastLocation">Museum (1978)</rs>.</p>
</div>





<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>Found during the clearing of the East Gate in 1904 and recorded by Gaudin (108), 'la face engagée dans la maçonnerie'; by the MAMA expedition; by the NYU expedition.</p>
</div>

